Of strategic and political significance, the conquest of space generated intense competition between the US and the then-Soviet Union during the Cold War. In 1957, the Soviets were first to place a satellite - Sputnik - into orbit. A weeks later, a dog became the first living creature in space. Laika did not survive the journey, and there was no way to bring her back to Earth. The Playboy Pictures That Went To The Moon In July 1969, the world watched as man first set foot on the Moon.